JDK 1.3.1 for Linux (from java.sun.com):

j2sdk-1_3_1-linux-i386.bin
j2re-1_3_1-linux-i386.bin (not necessary, jre comes with jdk)
j2sdk-1_3_1-doc.zip (don't bother, as 1.3.1 docs are already installed)

Installation instructions:
http://java.sun.com/j2se/1.3/install-linux-sdk.html#self-extracting

# In the future, I should install into a directory under /usr/local/pkg/java.

su
mv j2sdk-1_3_1-linux-i386.bin /g2
cd g2
chmod +x j2sdk-1_3_1-linux-i386.bin
./j2sdk-1_3_1-linux-i386.bin
# adjust links in ~mernst/java

===========================================================================

Install JDK 1.3 for Linux:
http://blackdown.org/java-linux/jdk1.2-status/jdk1.3-status.html
I installed 1.3.0-FCS.

## This was useless; it's already in /g2/jdoc/jdk1.3.
Documentation:
http://java.sun.com/j2se/1.3/index.html
Download the documentation in Zip format, NOT in tar format.
Unbundle it in /g2
jdk-add-munged-anchor-names `find /g2/jdk1.3/docs/api -name '*.html' -print`
# Or, if that command line is too long: find /g2/jdk1.3/docs/api -name '*.html' -print | xargs jdk-add-munged-anchor-names
# Now rerun jdk-index-to-alist.  Also add to `jdk-ignored-prefixes' in jdk-lookup.el.


===========================================================================

I was able to successfully install JDK 1.2.2 (unlike previous releases)

http://www.javasoft.com/products/jdk/1.2/download-solaris.html

[
 JDK source release: http://www.sun.com/software/communitysource/java2/
 It looks like I have copies of this in ~/se/.
 This is C source code for the Java virtual machine and runtime, etc.
 It may also be Java source code for javac, etc.
 Java source for libraries comes with the JDK in src.jar.
]

Download the JDK itself.
Download the documentation (in Zip format, NOT in tar format).

To install documentation: Basically, download and unbundle the
documentation in the same directory as the Java 2 SDK software.
(Actually, don't do that; we don't want documentation in
/uns/lib/ but in /cse/www/uns/.)

cd /uns/lib
chmod a+x /tmp/mernst/jdk1_2_2-solsparc.sh
/tmp/mernst/jdk1_2_2-solsparc.sh

# Adjust my personal symbolic links in ~/java and ~/lib/solaris:
cd ~/java
ln -s /uns/lib/jdk1.2.2 jdk1.2.2 
rm jdk1.2
ln -s jdk1.2.2 jdk1.2
cd ~/lib/solaris
ln -s /uns/lib/jdk1.2.2 jdk1.2.2 
rm jdk1.2
ln -s jdk1.2.2 jdk1.2

rehash
java -version

# Install the documentation.  (If I use tar format, then I end up with 13
# files at the top level and must move them by hand; so use zip format.)
## No, install it in /cse/www/uns/.
cd /uns/lib
unzip /tmp/mernst/jdk1_2_2-doc.zip
chgrp -R uns jdk1.2.2
chmod -R g+w jdk1.2.2

# Also in /projects/cse/www/uns/docs,
#  if not already there and if there is sufficient disk space.
# It would be better to share disk space (just unpack this once)
cd /projects/cse/www/uns/docs
unzip /tmp/mernst/jdk1_2_2-doc.zip
chgrp -R uns jdk1.2.2
chmod -R g+w jdk1.2.2
cd jdk1.2.2
mv docs/* .
rmdir docs
jdk-add-munged-anchor-names `find /projects/cse/www/uns/doc/jdk1.2.2/api -name '*.html' -print`
# Eventually, do  find . -name '*.bak' -print | xargs rm -f
# Now rerun jdk-index-to-alist.  Also add to `jdk-ignored-prefixes' in jdk-lookup.el.


If things go wrong, clean up:
  rm -rf /uns/lib/jdk1.2.2
  cd ~/java
  rm jdk1.2
  ln -s jdk1.2beta4 jdk1.2
  cd ~/lib/solaris
  rm jdk1.2
  ln -s jdk1.2beta4 jdk1.2

